[b]Explaining the code:[/b]
[code]if ((itemUsed == 249) && (useWith == 227)[/code]
This basically means if u use the herb on the vial of water (227) there will happen something (described farder in the code)

[code]|| (itemUsed == 227) && (useWith == 249)) {
[/code]
This means that the action also happens when using the water on the herb, so not only herb on water

[code]if (playerLevel[15] >= 1 [/code]
This says that the herblore level (15) has to be equal or bigger than 1 to do the action.

[code]deleteItem(249, getItemSlot(249), 1);
deleteItem(227, getItemSlot(227), 1);

[/code]
This makes that once u did the action the herb and the vial get removed out of your inventory

[code]addItem(2428, 1);[/code]
This says, if u did the action a potion gets added, 2428 is the potion ID; 1 is the quantity

[code]addSkillXP(2800, 15);[/code]
This makes that u gain experience once done the action; 2800 is the amount of xp, 15 is the skill level ID - herblore in this case

[code]setAnimation(1652);[/code]
This makes u doing an emote when the action happens; 1652 is the emote ID

[code]} else {
					sM("You need 1 herblore to make this potion.");
				}
			}
[/code]
This says, if the player doesn't have level 1 then the action will not happen and give them a message in their chat (sM) that they need this * level to make the potion.


[size=12pt][b]Now to make it a donator skill[/b][/size]

Scroll back in your code and everywhere where it says
[code]if (playerLevel[15] >= #) {[/code]
note: # is the required level

add [code]&& donator == 1[/code] in it

so it looks like this:
[code]if (playerLevel[15] >= # && donator == 1) {[/code]
This says that the action only can happen if the player is a donator


When u have done this everywhere, then move on to the next step:

Scroll back up till the start of your code, so under the last bracket of the last code, where u started herblore;
add this:

